<DocsPageTitle Path="Specifications/TreeView">
    Blazorise Specifications: TreeView
</DocsPageTitle>

<DocsPageLead>
    Learn how the TreeView behaves when selection, expansion, and virtualization are combined.
</DocsPageLead>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    SelectionMode
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    <Code>SelectionMode.Single</Code> uses <Code>SelectedNode</Code> and selection happens by clicking the node content.
    <Code>SelectionMode.Multiple</Code> uses <Code>SelectedNodes</Code> and selection happens via the checkbox; clicking node content does not toggle selection in multiple mode.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Disabled nodes from <Code>IsDisabled</Code> ignore clicks and checkbox changes and are styled through <Code>DisabledNodeStyling</Code>.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Expansion and ExpandedNodes
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Expanded state is tracked in <Code>ExpandedNodes</Code>. Toggling a node updates the list and raises <Code>ExpandedNodesChanged</Code>.
    When <Code>ExpandedNodes</Code> changes externally, the TreeView synchronizes expansion on the next parameter set and loads children for newly expanded nodes.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    <Code>AutoExpandAll</Code> runs only once during the initial load. It expands nodes that report children and updates <Code>ExpandedNodes</Code>.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Child Loading
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    Child nodes are loaded lazily using <Code>GetChildNodes</Code> or <Code>GetChildNodesAsync</Code> when a node expands.
    <Code>HasChildNodes</Code>/<Code>HasChildNodesAsync</Code> determines whether the expand toggle is shown.
</DocsPageParagraph>

<DocsPageSubtitle>
    Virtualize
</DocsPageSubtitle>

<DocsPageParagraph>
    When <Code>Virtualize</Code> is enabled, each expanded node list is rendered using Blazor's <Code>Virtualize</Code> component.
    If <Code>Height</Code> or <Code>Overflow</Code> are not explicitly set, the TreeView defaults to a height of 300px and <Code>Overflow.Auto</Code>.
</DocsPageParagraph>